In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims April 22, 2012, as Earth Day and encourages all Americans to participate in programs and activities that protect the environment and contribute to a healthy, sustainable future. The article reflects on the challenges that remain in environmental protection and highlights the progress that has been made, such as passing environmental protection acts, founding the Environmental Protection Agency, and reducing pollution. The Obama Administration's efforts to set tough fuel economy standards, limit toxic emissions from power plants, protect and restore ecosystems, and invest in renewable energy are also mentioned. The article emphasizes the importance of equipping future generations with the tools and knowledge to tackle environmental challenges and mentions the Department of Education Green Ribbon Schools recognition award for promoting sustainability and environmental literacy in schools. The article concludes by urging the commitment to leaving a safe and clean world for future generations.